  "prompt": "Being an engineer (not a student) how can i get an internship (preferably research) from iisc or iit?",
  "response": "As an experienced engineer seeking an internship or research opportunity at IISc or IITs, here are some strategies:\n\n1. Direct Contact Methods:\n- Email professors directly in your field of interest\n- Send a detailed CV highlighting your expertise\n- Explain your specific research interests\n- Attach any published papers/patents\n- Request a research collaboration or short-term internship\n\n2. Networking Approaches:\n- Attend conferences/seminars at IISc/IITs\n- Connect with alumni from these institutions\n- Use professional platforms like LinkedIn\n- Engage with research groups on social media\n\n3. Formal Channels:\n- Check official institute websites for research positions\n- Look for sponsored research project openings\n- Explore sponsored industrial research programs\n- Check individual department research call for proposals\n\n4. Research Funding Agencies:\n- Apply through SERB (Science & Engineering Research Board)\n- Explore DST (Department of Science & Technology) programs\n- Check CSIR (Council of Scientific & Industrial Research) opportunities\n\n5. Specific Application Strategies:\n- Highlight unique skills/expertise\n- Demonstrate previous research experience\n- Show alignment with lab/professor's research interests\n- Propose potential collaborative projects\n\n6. Additional Tips:\n- Be precise about duration and expectations\n- Demonstrate genuine research passion\n- Be open to unpaid/partially funded opportunities",
